title: 'Stop bringing people to take our jobs': Trump aide explains reason behind H1B fee hike

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: The sudden demise of singer Zubeen Garg in a Singapore scuba diving accident has deeply saddened fans and the music industry. Assam's Chief Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma is coordinating efforts to bring Garg's remains home, with a post-mortem scheduled in Singapore.
title: Zubeen Garg's body to be handed to India after Singapore post-mortem: Assam CM

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Navi Mumbai police have arrested Praful Salunkhe, the driver of former IAS probationer Puja Khedkar's father, in connection with the abduction of a truck driver following a road rage incident. The victim, Prahlad Kumar, was rescued from the Khedkar family bungalow in Pune, where Puja's mother allegedly obstructed police.
title: Hunt on for Puja Khedkar’s family: Navi Mumbai police arrest driver; mother, dad still absconding

author: GAURAV GUPTA
description: In a historic move, the Indian women's cricket team will don pink jerseys for the final ODI against Australia in Delhi, raising breast cancer awareness. This marks the first instance of an Indian cricket team sporting pink for this cause.
title: INDW vs AUSW: India to wear pink jerseys in breast cancer awareness initiative

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: OpenAI is aggressively poaching Apple employees and partnering with its suppliers, aiming to launch consumer hardware by late 2026. Led by former Apple executive Tang Tan, the recruitment drive has attracted talent in design, manufacturing, and engineering. OpenAI plans a family of screen-free, pocket-sized AI devices, challenging Apple's dominance and creating tension between the two companies.
title: iPhone to AI era: Man who helped build Apple’s icon; now stealing staff for OpenAI

title: 'National security': Why Trump imposed $100,000 fee per year on H-1B visas

author: AHMED ALI
description: A finance company director in Mumbai has filed a police complaint against Saurav Raidhani for alleged stalking and harassment. The accused, whom she initially connected with on LinkedIn, reportedly sent obscene messages and unwanted advances over two years. Despite being blocked, he allegedly used over 100 SIM cards to contact her, even tracking her movements abroad.
title: Over 100 SIMs, endless messages: Man stalked woman for more than 2 years on LinkedIn

author: TNN
description: Karnataka police have recovered a portion of the valuables stolen from the State Bank of India's Chadchan branch. The robbers, who fled to Maharashtra, abandoned part of their loot after a confrontation with villagers in Hulajanti village. The recovered bag contained 6.5 kg of gold jewellery and Rs 41 lakh in cash, according to Vijayapura SP Laxman Nimbargi.
title: SBI heist: Robbers abandon part of bank loot in Maha; Rs 41L cash, 6.5 kg gold recovered

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: The Income-Tax Department is cracking down on fraudulent tax exemption claims, estimated at ₹700 crore, leading to potential refund delays, especially for claims over Rs 10 lakh. Discrepancies include fabricated medical expenses and false donations, primarily under the old tax framework.
title: Slower tax refunds after ITR filing? IT dept detects false exemption claims of Rs 700cr

author: DHANANJAY MAHAPATRA AND MARCUS MERGULHAO
description: The Supreme Court has finalised the All India Football Federation's (AIFF) constitution, mirroring the BCCI framework, barring ministers and bureaucrats from management and setting a 70-year age cap. The AIFF must adopt the revised constitution within four weeks, potentially by October 14 in Goa, to avoid FIFA suspension.
title: Supreme Court approves AIFF constitution; 70-year age cap

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Suryakumar Yadav's continued refusal to acknowledge Pakistan fuels the anticipation for their Super 4 clash in the Asia Cup 2025. India secured a narrow victory against Oman, topping Group A, but the focus remains on the high-stakes encounter with their arch-rivals. Yadav's curt responses and previous controversies add extra spice to the upcoming showdown.
title: Did Suryakumar Yadav snub Pakistan again? India captain avoids naming arch-rivals

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Microsoft urged its H-1B and H-4 visa employees to return to the US before the September 21 deadline due to a new $100,000 annual fee per H-1B worker. The company also advised those already in the US to remain there.
title: H1-B visa fees hike to $100K: Microsoft warns employees; asks to return immediately

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A soldier critically wounded in a gunfight with terrorists in the Udhampur district of Jammu and Kashmir on Friday evening has died. The gunfight broke out during a joint search operation by the Army and J&K Police in the Seoj Dhar forest area. Security forces have cordoned off the area and are continuing search operations for the two to three terrorists believed to be hiding in the difficult terrain.
title: J&K: Soldier killed in gunfight in Udhampur; hunt for terrorists resumes

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Donald Trump has introduced the "Trump Gold Card," an immigration initiative offering wealthy individuals and corporations fast-tracked US residency. Priced at $1 million for individuals and $2 million per employee for corporations, it promises accelerated processing under EB-1 or EB-2 visa categories. The program aims to generate billions in revenue, potentially reducing taxes and debt.
title: Trump’s $1 million gold card visa: Who qualifies, what it offers – Here’s how to apply

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: A heated dispute has erupted between the PCB and ICC over alleged protocol breaches during a recent Dubai match. The controversy centers on the PCB media manager's unauthorized mobile phone use in the PMOA, a violation of anti-corruption guidelines. While the PCB defends its position, ICC regulations strictly prohibit such usage, escalating tensions further as the Asia Cup clash approaches.
title: What is PMOA, which Pakistan cricket board is alleged to have breached? Explained

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The US department of labour has launched "Project Firewall" to target H-1B visa misuse, aligning with President Trump's "America First" agenda. This initiative aims to protect American workers by scrutinising companies hiring foreign employees and ensuring fair wages. The secretary of labour will personally oversee investigations, with violators facing penalties like back wage repayment and program debarment, impacting industries heavily reliant on H-1B workers, especially Indian nationals.
title: Immigration crackdown: H-1B visas to cost more, move to impact Indians – 'Project Firewall' explained

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: NASA's advanced observatories have unveiled the Milky Way's hidden beauty, from its dense core with a supermassive black hole to glittering star clusters and spiral arms. Infrared cameras pierce through gas and dust, revealing millions of stars. These images help astronomers study star formation, galactic dynamics, and the future collision with Andromeda, enhancing our understanding of our galactic home.
title: Nasa shares Milky Way photos: Star clusters revealed; galaxy’s hidden core

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: SpaceX is set to upgrade mobile connectivity with a $17 billion acquisition of airwave licenses from EchoStar, enabling seamless satellite internet on mobile phones, even in remote areas. This move allows SpaceX to bypass traditional cell towers and directly connect to Starlink satellites, potentially disrupting telecom giants.
title: SpaceX’s $17 bn plan: Musk targets trekking lovers; Here’s what it means for travel

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Counter Intelligence Kashmir conducted searches at multiple locations across seven districts in the Valley on Saturday, targeting terror-related activities. The coordinated operation spanned eight locations in Srinagar, Baramulla, Anantnag, Kupwara, Handwara, Pulwama, and Shopian, following warrants obtained from a competent court. This crackdown follows a deadly terror attack in April where 26 civilians were killed in Anantnag.
title: Terror case: J&K CIK raids across Valley; Srinagar, Pulwama, Anantnag among districts targeted

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce, engaged since August, are reportedly planning an intimate wedding for early next year. While no venue is set, Rhode Island is a potential location. Swift is enjoying the creative process, with designers eager to create her gown, but the couple prioritizes a meaningful celebration with loved ones over a lavish spectacle.
title: Travis Kelce & Taylor Swift: From wedding rumours to surprise timeline

author: ABHINAV GARG
description: Saikat Basu is desperately seeking the return of his five-year-old son, Stavyo, after his estranged wife, Viktoriia, allegedly fled to Russia with the child in violation of Supreme Court orders. Basu claims Russian embassy personnel aided her departure from India. He emphasizes his focus is solely on reuniting with his son, highlighting Viktoriia's alleged negligence and cruelty towards Stavyo.
title: ‘Viktoriia’s Secret’: Man seeks reunion with son; Russian wife flees with child to Moscow

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: During the Asia Cup clash against Oman, Axar Patel sustained a head injury while fielding, though he is reportedly "doing fine," according to India's fielding coach. Despite the setback, India secured a 21-run victory over Oman. Sanju Samson and Abhishek Sharma's contributions helped India post a total of 188/8. Arshdeep Singh also celebrated claiming his 100th T20I wicket.
title: Will Axar Patel miss Pakistan match after head blow? Latest update

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Oman opener Aamir Kaleem etched his name in cricket history by becoming the oldest batter to score a half-century against India, surpassing a 79-year-old record. His impressive 64-run innings against India marked a historic moment, also making him the oldest to hit a T20I fifty against a full member nation.
title: Aamir Kaleem becomes oldest batter to score fifty vs India; breaks 79-year record

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Sunil Gavaskar defended Suryakumar Yadav's choice to not bat against Oman, citing his unorthodox thinking and potential strategy to test Kuldeep Yadav's batting. Rohan Gavaskar questioned the move, suggesting Rinku Singh should have been given a chance instead. Despite the debate, India secured a 21-run victory, with experts highlighting Yadav's innovative captaincy and willingness to take risks.

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Several schools in Delhi, including DPS Dwarka and Krishna Model Public School, received bomb threat calls on Saturday, leading to immediate evacuations and extensive security sweeps. This incident follows a similar bomb threat at the Delhi High Court eight days prior, where an email alluded to a potential blast and alleged connections to Pakistani intelligence.
title: Multiple Delhi schools receive bomb threats; students, staff evacuated

author: APEKSHA TANWAR
description: President Trump has raised the H-1B visa sponsorship fee to $100,000 to prioritise American jobs and curb outsourcing. Indian professionals, who form the majority of H-1B holders, may face reduced opportunities, especially in junior roles. The change pressures companies like Amazon, Microsoft, and TCS to reconsider hiring strategies, shifting focus to highly specialised, high-wage talent and domestic graduates.
title: Trump protects US jobs: H-1B fee hiked; what changes for Indian workers

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: President Trump introduced the "Gold Card Visa," offering expedited US residency for wealthy individuals and corporations investing significant sums. The Gold Card requires a $1 million contribution, while the Platinum Card, pending approval, demands $5 million with tax benefits. Revenue will fund commerce promotion and debt reduction, potentially reshaping immigration policy by replacing existing visa programs.

description: After Oman’s spirited fight against India, captain Jatinder Singh thanked Suryakumar Yadav for his post-match pep talk, calling it invaluable for his young side.
